{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"046a79cb-6ae9-40ad-982d-06b144b38d5c","content":"Here's my analysis of the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n## 1. Deep Import Chain (High Impact)\n\nThe project imports `level1.props`, which imports `level2.props`, which imports `level3.props`. This 3-level deep chain forces MSBuild's **evaluation phase** to recursively open, parse, and evaluate each file before it can proceed. Each import adds file I/O and XML parsing overhead. In larger projects this nesting can grow much deeper and significantly slow evaluation.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten the chain — import all `.props` files directly from the `.csproj`, or consolidate them into a single file.\n\n## 2. Overly Broad Glob Pattern (High Impact)\n\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n\nThe `**\\*.*` glob recursively scans the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. It will traverse `.git/`, `node_modules/`, and any other large directories. Only `bin` and `obj` are excluded.\n\n**Fix:** Restrict the glob to specific extensions/folders, or add more exclusions via `DefaultItemExcludes`:\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.cs;**\\*.json\" />\n```\n\n## 3. File I/O via Property Function During Evaluation (Medium Impact)\n\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n\nThis uses a property function to perform **disk I/O during the evaluation phase**. MSBuild evaluation should be lightweight (resolving properties, items, imports). File reads belong in the **execution phase** (targets/tasks). If the file is large or on a slow disk, this blocks evaluation.\n\n**Fix:** Move the file read into a target that runs during build execution:\n```xml\n<Target Name=\"ReadBuildNotes\" BeforeTargets=\"Build\">\n  <ReadLinesFromFile File=\"build-notes.txt\">\n    <Output TaskParameter=\"Lines\" PropertyName=\"BuildNotes\"/>\n  </ReadLinesFromFile>\n</Target>\n```\n\n---\n\n**Key concept:** MSBuild's *evaluation phase* (processing imports, properties, items, globs) runs before any targets execute. Work done here cannot be parallelized and blocks all downstream operations, so keeping it lean is critical for build performance.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3a631f38-0de7-4fa9-9fa1-4bae719169f9","outputTokens":561,"requestId":"7C13:389F98:BEC236:DAD7AA:6A02802C"},"id":"283e4333-2e5c-47e4-9171-7dbf52b3d06e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:19:54.308Z","parentId":"66c3f075-63d7-43db-9530-f390153ec714"}
